# Cloud Security & Infrastructure Hardening Lab

## Overview

This project demonstrates hands-on cloud security implementation using Azure virtual machines and Linux-based security hardening techniques.

The lab simulates real-world attack detection and automated defense mechanisms.

---

## Environment

- Microsoft Azure VM (Ubuntu 22.04)
- Wazuh SIEM (Manager + Agent)
- UFW Firewall
- Fail2Ban
- Public-facing SSH server

---

## Implementations

### 1. SIEM Deployment
- Installed Wazuh Manager
- Deployed Wazuh Agent
- Monitored authentication logs
- Verified agent connectivity

### 2. Brute Force Detection
- Detected repeated SSH login attempts
- Identified malicious IP addresses
- Observed rule triggers (Rule 5710 and related authentication rules)

### 3. File Integrity Monitoring (FIM)
- Enabled syscheck
- Monitored /etc directory
- Triggered real-time file modification alerts

### 4. Host Firewall Hardening
- Enabled UFW
- Allowed SSH securely
- Implemented rate limiting:
  
  sudo ufw limit 22/tcp
  
- Manually blocked malicious IP addresses

### 5. Automatic Protection with Fail2Ban
- Installed and configured Fail2Ban
- Monitored /var/log/auth.log
- Automatically banned brute-force attackers
- Verified banned IP list

